{
  "texts": [
    "PTQ-based methodsIn PTQ-based methods, we first quantize an LLM and then fine-tune the quantized model, namely quantization and finetuning are sequentially conducted.",
    "QLoRA [91] is the first PTQ-based quantization-aware LoRA method.",
    "In the finetuning stage, it first quantizes an LLM to 4 bits and then finetunes a LoRA module on it with a higher precision, such as BFloat16 or Float16.",
    "In the inference stage, it dequantizes the LLM to the same precision as LoRA and then adds the LoRA updates to the LLM.Although QLoRA can significantly reduce memory cost for fine-tuning, it does not bring benefits for inference, because it requires dequantizing the LLM to high precision again.",
    "To solve this problem, QA-LoRA [92] is proposed to reduce memory cost for both the fine-tuning and inference stages."
  ]
}